{
  "texts": [
    "The proposed algorithm is the first to have non-asymptotic convergence guarantees (black).",
    "Existing algorithms in similar settings are only known to converge asymptotically (red).",
    "Convergence rate of a single-loop algorithm for bi-level optimization [Hong et al., 2023] under a nonconvex upper-level objective and lowerlevel strong convexity (blue).We introduce AC-SMFG, a single-loop actor-critic algorithm for SMFGs which operates under continuously generated Markovian samples.",
    "Our first key contribution is to characterize the finite-time and finite-sample complexity of AC-SMFG.",
    "We achieve this through a multi-time-scale analysis, where the updates of the leader's policy, the follower's policy, and the mean field are coordinated on distinct time scales via properly chosen step sizes."
  ]
}